  "analysis_prompt": {
    "global_feedback_guidance": "Prioritize reusable AI visual effects driving social sharing, specifically retro cinema posters, friend-to-couple transformations, emotional/childhood-adult portraits, and modular high-fidelity prompts. Explicitly recognize low-friction static-to-dance/photo-to-video AI tools as high-potential formats due to minimal user effort and strong viral replication, but apply a medium/watch stance when content relies heavily on copyrighted IPs or music. Favor one-click template tools with strong aesthetic or relationship hooks. Recognize strong visual contrast effects (e.g., origami texture, handcraft illusions) as high-potential ad creatives. Accept sports star debut posters when driven by accessible template tools. Reject region-specific cinematic styles (e.g., Bollywood movie subtitles, regional star portraits) unless they demonstrate global template reuse. Demote high-execution complexity, saturated duplicate outputs, and complex biometric fusions.",
    "ua_guidance": "UA feedback should favor clear first-three-second hooks, prompt/template shareability, immediate visual payoff, low user friction for UGC replication, and broad creative applicability across demographics. Note IP/music dependencies as constraints that may limit mass adoption, warranting a 'medium' rating even if viral.",
    "product_guidance": "Product feedback should favor reusable video and image effects, portrait enhancements, emotion/nostalgia-driven templates, and modular prompt workflows that drive social sharing and template reuse. Highlight tools that abstract backend complexity into simple upload-and-generate flows. Prioritize content with enough comment activity to indicate real discussion, and avoid treating ordinary celebrity, hardware, generic tech news, creator milestone/subscriber celebration posts, or cinematic superhero/power-fantasy prompt posts as product opportunities unless the post itself clearly demonstrates reusable product value.",
    "risk_guidance": "Exclude NSFW, soft-porn, edge-bait, bikini/swimsuit beach-girl bait, AI-girl bait, and anime soft-porn visual content rather than merely demoting it. Exclude creator follower/subscriber milestone posts such as 100k club or subscribe-button celebrations even when a prompt is attached. Demote low-reuse, controversial, duplicated, weak-quality, low-comment-rate, or high-execution-barrier topics. Flag saturated formats, IP-dependent challenges, cartoon/animal dance clips with weak product transfer, and complex visual fusions that yield diminishing returns or high user drop-off. Treat IP-reliant viral trends as watchlist items rather than hard rejects if user friction is low.",
    "priority_guidance": "高=strong accept (prioritize), 中=watch (context-dependent or higher execution barrier/IP constraints), 低=weak accept, 否决=demote or exclude."
