    "2026-06-02 feedback: High acceptance for Hypic/Gemini AI photo editing templates with one-click generation and clear CTA links, highlighting low-friction UGC replication. Reject advertising-specific storyboards (e.g., Coke ads on wavespeed) as they lack reusable product value for general users. Medium/watch for summer luxury resort/vacation AI portrait effects due to regional appeal but lower global trend velocity.",
    "2026-06-03 feedback: High acceptance for childhood photo-to-video, royal/cultural portrait templates, and sports debut posters. Reject commercial advertising storyboards (e.g., Fanta/Picsart Flow) and high-difficulty casual avatar generation. Rain couple/portrait remains excluded despite isolated product interest due to saturation and low UA novelty.",
    "2026-06-04 manual table feedback: rows 9/11/15 are low quality. Reject generic high-fidelity AI portrait prompt or face-lock prompt posts without strong before/after, upload/template UI, or clear Evoke/Toki/Kavi/Avatar product mechanic; reject one-click makeup/beauty-filter/try-on clips as weak product material unless they show a distinctive reusable AI transformation beyond cosmetic retouching; reject baseball spectator/broadcast-girl or sports fan-edit derivatives unless the user-upload identity transformation, prompt workflow, and product template value are explicit.",
    "2026-06-04 feedback: Reject specific ethnic/cultural bridal portraits (e.g., Nepali traditional bridal) generated via Hypic due to potential cultural sensitivity or lack of broad reusable product value, despite high engagement and prompt requests.",
    "2026-06-05 feedback: Today's pushed rows 2 and 3 were Gemini Rain / AI couple embrace in the rain templates that have already been covered. Treat Google Gemini Rain, Gemini Rain AI Effect/Filter, AIrain/rainAIeffect, rainy embrace, and portraits in the rain as saturated duplicate low-quality material, even if comments and template demand are high.",
